<hr>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
Do not italicize the titles of blog posts, online forums messages, comments, status updates, etc.<br> 
Italicize titles of reports and other documents that stand alone.<br> 
If the distinction is unclear err on the side of not italicizing.<br> 
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Organisation. (Publication date). Title of web page. Retrieved from URL
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Organisation">The Turning Page Bookshop</span>. 
	(<span class="hover" title="Publication date">2056</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of web page">Business profile</span>.  
	Retrieved from <span class="hover" title="URL">http://www.theturningpagebookshop.com.au/</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
Note: this example differs from referencing an 
<a href="%%ICiteURL%%/3/2?width=800&amp;height=600" class="colorbox-node">
	Electronic Article, Internet Journal Article
</a>.
<br>
For more information on referencing websites see the <a href='http://west-sydney-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/UWS-ALMA:default_scope:UWS-ALMA5196906240001571'>APA guide to electronic 
References</a>.
<br> 
See also the online APA style blog entry: <a href='http://blog.apastyle.org/apastyle/2010/11/how-to-cite-something-you-found-on-a-website-in-apa-style.html'>How to cite something you found on a website in APA Style</a>
