<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
Use the organisation&#8217;s name as the author name (organisations include private companies, 
government agencies and institutions).
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	The Turning Page Bookshop (2056) explains that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: &hellip;outlined in their business profile (The Turning Page Bookshop, 2056).
</blockquote>
<br>
Where it is possible to abbreviate the organisation&#8217;s name, in the first citation write the 
organisation name in full, including the abbreviation in square brackets. After that, use 
the abbreviation.
<br>
<strong>First in&#45;text citation</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;as a recent study has shown (Department of Education, Employment and Workplace Relations
	[DEEWR], 2056).
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Subsequent in&#45;text citations</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;as recent evidence suggests (DEEWR, 2056).
</blockquote>
<br>
The name of the University of Western Sydney should be written out in full.
<br>
<strong>All text citations</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	(The University of Western Sydney, 2056)
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	The Department of Education, Employment and Workplace Relations [DEEWR] (2056) reports that 
	&#34;government funding has been reduced by 15%&#34;.
	<br>
	Alternatively: As a result, &#34;government funding has been reduced by 15%&#34; 
	(Department of Education, Employment and Workplace Relations [DEEWR], 2056).
</blockquote>
<br>
If you wish to cite an <strong>entire website</strong> it is not necessary to include the website 
in your Reference List. Just add the URL for the site in text.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Workcover is a useful work health and safety website for information and documents about 
	addiction (http://www.workcover.nsw.gov.au/newlegislation2012/Pages/default.aspx)
</blockquote>
